items.sentence: I don\'t think that Tom has to go there by himself.
I don\'t think that Tom has very many friends here.
I don\'t think that Tom knows Mary as well as I do.
I don\'t think that Tom knows how much Mary weighs.
I don\'t think that Tom knows how to play the oboe.
Tom managed to do everything he was supposed to do.
Tom was about to be kissed, but he didn\'t know it.
Have you decided on where you\'re going to do that?
Tom graduated from college at the top of his class.
Did you have toast for breakfast yesterday morning?
